On March 20, 2015, the President signed H.R. 1213 into law. This law extends the term of certain members of the Board of Directors of the Office of Compliance in the Legislative Branch for an additional two years. The Office of Compliance administers the application of certain Federal laws related to civil rights, labor, and workplace safety and health to the Legislative Branch. The law also makes changes to procedures for mediation and hearings administered by the Office of Compliance.